         "id": "SECTION_local_content",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<h3>Gravity as a Central Force</h3>When we talk about gravity as a force in Newton’s model, we often simplify things, and these simplifications can sometimes lead to misunderstandings. For example, it’s common to hear that the \"gravitational force\" pulls objects \"downward\", which is imprecise and might cause some people to think of Earth as flat. The \"gravitational force\" is a central force that attracts objects toward Earth’s center",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "9f86c1c9-1fd7-4d22-95f6-a1b5ed13b1ee",
                     "text": "Newton, Isaac",
                     "page": "pp. 3",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "1686",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "1df98dc5-523f-42ae-9a69-3e9410849ebb",
                     "text": "Hossenfelder, Sabine",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2024",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "a6be3657-2567-4db5-b645-d5f65ea957fa",
                     "text": "Tong, David",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2013",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": "."
            },
            {
               "text": "Finally, we’d like to use this gravitational model to address a question I’ve often received: \"If the Earth isn’t flat, why don’t we fall off it in certain places?\" According to Newton’s gravitational model, escaping Earth’s surface requires moving at a very high speed. Without reaching this speed, known as escape velocity, gravity keeps us grounded on Earth",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "2451d5b3-6232-435b-9505-750b7459fdfe",
                     "text": "Britannica, The Editors of Encyclopaedia",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2024",
                        "month": "09",
                        "day": "20"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": "."
            },
            {
               "text": "<p>We will discuss the concept of a flat Earth in more detail later.</p>",
               "source": [],
